.com\">Visual Composer Website Builder</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"Irma Edite Girupniece\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11603:\"<div class=\"vce-row-container\" data-vce-boxed-width=\"true\"><div class=\"vce-row vce-row--col-gap-30 vce-row-equal-height vce-row-content--top\" id=\"el-cfd670c3\" data-vce-do-apply=\"all el-cfd670c3\"><div class=\"vce-row-content\" data-vce-element-content=\"true\"><div class=\"vce-col vce-col--md-auto vce-col--xs-1 vce-col--xs-last vce-col--xs-first vce-col--sm-last vce-col--sm-first vce-col--md-last vce-col--lg-last vce-col--xl-last vce-col--md-first vce-col--lg-first vce-col--xl-first\" id=\"el-37a1f300\"><div class=\"vce-col-inner\" data-vce-do-apply=\"border margin background  el-37a1f300\"><div class=\"vce-col-content\" data-vce-element-content=\"true\" data-vce-do-apply=\"padding el-37a1f300\"><div class=\"vce-text-block\"><div class=\"vce-text-block-wrapper vce\" id=\"el-a973c438\" data-vce-do-apply=\"all el-a973c438\"><p>The internet is a vast place with endless possibilities. In recent years, the rise of websites has been incredible. Today, there are more than 2 billion active websites online and that number will continue to grow. With so many options available for building your own website, it can be hard to know which one to choose. But what if I told you that you could build your WordPress site faster than before? Well, it\'s possible and I\'m going to show you how!</p><p>The trick is choosing the right tools that allow optimizing the time you need to create a website. And what are the main components of a website design? Layout, graphic assets, content, and SEO. Luckily, I\'ve got a tool for every one of these components wrapped in a cozy Visual Composer blanket. All these tools can be used together in the new Visual Composer front-end editor, so you\'ll have everything at your fingertips at all times.</p><p>I\'ll show you how to create a full page quickly from start to finish using these tools:</p><ul><li>Visual Composer - a website builder for the layout</li><li>Unsplash integration - a free stock image library for images</li><li>Bertha AI assistant - for AI-generated content writing</li><li>Visual Composer Insights - a content analysis tool for SEO</li></ul><h2>Choose a layout with Visual Composer</h2><p>The first step in this whole process is to get your hands on Visual Composer. In this scenario, it will serve as the base of everything else. You can create your website from scratch using the plethora of features that Visual Composer has, but today we\'re here for speed. So the easiest and fastest way to start is to use one of the 10 templates available for the free version or one of the 200+ templates available for the premium version.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-33145\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Visual-Composer-Hub.png\" alt=\"Visual Composer Templates\" width=\"985\" height=\"625\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Visual-Composer-Hub.png 985w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Visual-Composer-Hub-300x190.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Visual-Composer-Hub-768x487.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Visual-Composer-Hub-848x538.png 848w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 985px) 100vw, 985px\" /></p><p>Once you\'ve chosen the right template for you, the next step is to simply change the content to fit what you want to display on your page. And not only that, you can change any single aspect of the template design - change the order of sections, change images and text, change fonts, sizes of sections, add more sections, and anything else that you see fit. So let\'s move on to just that.</p><h2>Generate content with Bertha AI</h2><p>AI is a very trendy topic at the moment and for a good reason - it just makes our lives easier.</p><p>As I mentioned earlier, <a href=\"https://bertha.ai/\">Bertha</a> is an AI-based writing assistant for WordPress that can generate high-quality content for you in seconds! Simply choose a topic from the list of available topics and let this artificial intelligence write about it. Bertha also has a free and premium version with the difference being the word count that the tool generates.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-33140\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Bertha-sub-heading.png\" alt=\"Bertha AI sub-heading template\" width=\"800\" height=\"463\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Bertha-sub-heading.png 800w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Bertha-sub-heading-300x174.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Bertha-sub-heading-768x444.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" /></p><p>The great thing about Bertha and Visual Composer is that you can use the writing assistant in the editor anywhere there\'s text. If we take a simple Text Block element as an example, when you open the edit window of that element, you\'ll see the Bertha icon. When you click on it, a sidebar with the possible type of content <em>(templates)</em> that it can generate will appear. This varies from Call to Action Button and Section Title, to full-on about us page and even a mission statement so you don’t have to think about that either!</p><p>All you have to do is introduce Bertha to what you\'ll be writing about and the AI assistant will generate content.</p><h2>Change images with Unsplash</h2><p>The next step in this journey is changing the template default images to images that fit your design ideas. Photoshoots take time and money so I\'m offering an easier way to customize the template.</p><p>This is where Unsplash can help. You can find the whole Unsplash image library in the <a href=\"help/visual-composer-hub/\">Visual Composer Hub</a>. Once you\'ve found an image, you can just click on it to download and it will be automatically added to your WordPress media library. No need to name new folders and save anything locally, the images are ready to use almost instantly.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-33141\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Unsplash.png\" alt=\"Unsplash\" width=\"900\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Unsplash.png 900w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Unsplash-300x125.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Unsplash-768x320.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Unsplash-848x353.png 848w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></p><p>Unsplash is a great source for finding royalty-free photos that fit any niche imaginable: from business websites to food blogs or travel magazines - there\'s an image for everyone here! So simply browse through the library, search for some keywords that are appropriate for you.</p><p>When you\'ve got your images, you can\'t always rely on what the photographer had in mind with the coloring of it. So there are actually a couple of ways you can spice up these stock photos to fit the style of your page.</p><p>First are the <a href=\"blog/instagram-like-filters-feature/\">Instagram-like filters</a> for Single Image elements. Apply a filter that you like most and the images will have a coherent look.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-33142\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Instagram-like-filters.png\" alt=\"Instagram-like filters\" width=\"900\" height=\"536\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Instagram-like-filters.png 900w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Instagram-like-filters-300x179.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Instagram-like-filters-768x457.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Instagram-like-filters-848x505.png 848w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></p><p>The second is the <a href=\"help/design-options/background-color-css-gradient-background/\">Gradient Overlay</a> for backgrounds. If you set an image as a background for any row or column, you can add an overlay and it will change the look completely.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-33143\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Gradient-overlay.png\" alt=\"Gradient overlay\" width=\"1000\" height=\"505\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Gradient-overlay.png 1000w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Gradient-overlay-300x152.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Gradient-overlay-768x388.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Gradient-overlay-848x428.png 848w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> This is the only feature available only for the Premium version of Visual Composer. Although you can still get free images from the <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Unsplash</a> website, Visual Composer just makes it quicker and easier.</p><h2>SEO with Insights</h2><p>The final tool we\'re going to look at is <a href=\"blog/wordpress-content-analysis-tool-insights/\">Visual Composer Insights</a>. It\'s a built-in content analysis tool that analyzes the content on your page and gives suggestions that can improve SEO and the performance of your site. And same as with all other tools that I talked about, you can find it in the Visual Composer editor. Just click on the bell icon in the navbar and you\'ll see all it has to offer.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-33144\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Insights.png\" alt=\"Insights\" width=\"600\" height=\"505\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Insights.png 600w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Insights-300x253.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> If there are any problems that Insights detects, there\'s going to be a red dot on the bell icon, so you know immediately.</p><p>With Insights, you\'ll see critical problems in red, warnings in yellow, and successes in green. And the scenarios that Insights check differ from checking if the text length is optimal, if the ALT attribute is missing for images, if the H1 title exists, to even checking the contrast on your page.</p><p>Insights will also show you exactly where on your page the problem is detected so you don\'t have to look for it yourself.</p><p>So if you\'re still questioning why this is so important, I\'m going to simply say - Google. If you want your page to be easily discoverable, it has to follow the best practices that Google\'s algorithm takes into account when figuring out where in the search results to put your site.</p><p>And once all the problems are gone and all you see is the green little Insights circle, you can pat yourself on the shoulder and be done with the page!</p><h2>Conclusion</h2><p>We\'ve gone on a full journey of creating a page using Visual Composer, Bertha AI, Unsplash, and Insights. A great bundle of tools that allow creating sites faster than before. I hope you\'ll try these out and add them to your routine as I have.</p><p>What do you do to make websites quicker? Let us know in the comments.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/how-to-create-a-wordpress-website-quickly-and-efficiently/\">How to Create a WordPress Website Quickly and Efficiently: The Tools I Used</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com\">Visual Composer Website Builder</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/how-to-create-a-wordpress-website-quickly-and-efficiently/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"Launch a Visual Composer Website on Cloudways in 1-Click\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/visual-composer-on-cloudways/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/visual-composer-on-cloudways/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 29 Oct 2021 08:06:15 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Cloudways\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Hosting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"https://visualcomposer.com/?p=33093\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:519:\"<p>In this review, we’ll describe the features that converted us to Cloudways, their customizable hosting plans, and what sets them apart from the competition. We’ll also show you how to set up your Visual Composer website on the platform.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/visual-composer-on-cloudways/\">Launch a Visual Composer Website on Cloudways in 1-Click</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com\">Visual Composer Website Builder</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"Visual Composer Staff\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38463:\"<div class=\"vce-row-container\" data-vce-boxed-width=\"true\"><div class=\"vce-row vce-row--col-gap-30 vce-row-equal-height vce-row-content--top\" id=\"el-3a5cfc73\" data-vce-do-apply=\"all el-3a5cfc73\"><div class=\"vce-row-content\" data-vce-element-content=\"true\"><div class=\"vce-col vce-col--md-auto vce-col--xs-1 vce-col--xs-last vce-col--xs-first vce-col--sm-last vce-col--sm-first vce-col--md-last vce-col--lg-last vce-col--xl-last vce-col--md-first vce-col--lg-first vce-col--xl-first\" id=\"el-a4dce887\"><div class=\"vce-col-inner\" data-vce-do-apply=\"border margin background  el-a4dce887\"><div class=\"vce-col-content\" data-vce-element-content=\"true\" data-vce-do-apply=\"padding el-a4dce887\"><div class=\"vce-text-block\"><div class=\"vce-text-block-wrapper vce\" id=\"el-67ef1a0e\" data-vce-do-apply=\"all el-67ef1a0e\"><p>When it comes to cloud hosting, there’s no dearth of options available in the market - all of which are quick to swear customizable plans, maximum uptime, user-friendliness, and a score of other features they may or may not deliver. With a field growing as fast as web hosting, it takes a little extra oomph to stand out among the competition.</p><p>We checked out Cloudways, now a major player in the industry, to see how it lives up to its name. <em>(Spoiler alert: we’re impressed enough to recommend it to all our Visual Composer users, whether you’re an agency or business owner, designer or developer, marketer or freelancer).</em></p><p>Let’s jump right in.</p><h2>Cloudways Overview</h2><p>Here’s the basic rundown off the bat: Cloudways offers managed hosting solutions with a spotlight shining bright on ease of use, choice, and performance. Activities like launching a server or application are incredibly simple to execute through 1-click operations, even for those of you who don’t have a degree in computer programming. Users get to choose between cloud providers, style of workflows, and extremely customizable hosting plans. And once you get your website running on Cloudways, the risk of your visitors seeing a 404 page all but vanishes.</p><p>In other words, the whole idea behind Cloudways is to leave the headache of server management to it, so you free up time to devote to your work instead.</p><h2>What Cloudways Have Going For Them</h2><p>Cloudways combines an excellent mix of features to optimize just about any site’s performance - agency, business, developer, or marketer. While it misses out on domain registration and email accounts, you’re likely to find it more than makes up for those in other aspects.</p><h3>Ease of Use</h3><p>From the get-go, it becomes quite obvious that Cloudways is explicitly designed to be easy to use. Signing up for either a 3-trial or a plan is a fast and simple process, as is creating a dedicated server. An average of ten minutes is all it takes to select the resources you need plus the server location <em>(for best results, choose the one closest to your physical location)</em>. Installing an application is a matter of a few clicks on the user panel.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-33293\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/get-started-with-Cloudways-1.jpg\" alt=\"Cloudways hosting one click installation\" width=\"700\" height=\"690\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/get-started-with-Cloudways-1.jpg 880w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/get-started-with-Cloudways-1-300x296.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/get-started-with-Cloudways-1-768x758.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/get-started-with-Cloudways-1-848x836.jpg 848w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></p><p>Cloudways’ 1-click installation for WordPress websites made in Visual Composer is sure to be a major draw - it eases the whole process even for developers. As for the user panel, it has a sleek design that’s easy to navigate, and which lets you monitor your server and applications, manage security settings, scale according to your needs, and more. And then there’s also access to SSH and FTP if you need to execute more complicated tasks on the server.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-33294 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-master-credentials.png\" alt=\"Master credentials in Cloudways settings\" width=\"1346\" height=\"426\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-master-credentials.png 1346w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-master-credentials-300x95.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-master-credentials-1024x324.png 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-master-credentials-768x243.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-master-credentials-848x268.png 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-master-credentials-1140x361.png 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-master-credentials-1170x370.png 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1346px) 100vw, 1346px\" /></p><h3>Customer Service and Technical Support</h3><p>Cloudways offers round-the-clock customer support through its chat option that links you directly with a customer service representative. It took no longer than 5 seconds to reach someone who was ready to take a question from us. We asked them about the company’s hosting plans, its payment structure, and then some slightly more technical questions about the hosting stack and security.</p><p>However, speaking to a person is a more involved process - you first have to fill out a form to request a call.</p><h3>Security</h3><p>According to Cloudways, it’s fully encrypted end-to-end and releases regular updates to the firmware and operating system. They also offer free SSL certificates - a must for all our e-commerce and online store operators - and all accounts come with a host of security features including firewalls, bot protection, two-factor authentication, and more.</p><h3>Advanced Features</h3><p>As mentioned above a few times, Cloudways uses its 1-Click operation to great effect. We especially liked how easy it was to scale server resources with just a few clicks. This is bound to be a great help whenever you experience an uptick in traffic and need to adjust your resources. Even if you’re only scaling for a week or so, like for Black Friday, their pay-as-you-go system means you’ll only be paying for the resources you consume.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-33295 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-advanced-features-1.jpg\" alt=\"Advanced features in Cloudways settings\" width=\"1459\" height=\"650\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-advanced-features-1.jpg 1459w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-advanced-features-1-300x134.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-advanced-features-1-1024x456.jpg 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-advanced-features-1-768x342.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-advanced-features-1-848x378.jpg 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-advanced-features-1-1140x508.jpg 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-advanced-features-1-1170x521.jpg 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1459px) 100vw, 1459px\" /></p><p>We’re also big fans of Cloudways’ server monitoring, which makes it simple for even non-tech savvy users to monitor a number of variables like Idle CPU and incoming traffic, all in easy-to-read graph form. You can surveil RAM, CPU, bandwidth, disk storage, database, and caching services using the relevant monitoring section of the server. What’s more, Cloudways has server monitoring alerts enabled across all servers and accounts, so you remain aware of non-contact with the server before your site visitors do.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-33296\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-monitoring-1024x818.jpg\" alt=\"Server monitoring in Cloudways settings\" width=\"900\" height=\"719\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-monitoring-1024x818.jpg 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-monitoring-300x240.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-monitoring-768x614.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-monitoring-848x678.jpg 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-monitoring-1140x911.jpg 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-monitoring-1170x935.jpg 1170w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-monitoring.jpg 1415w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></p><p>Oh, and you can set up automatic backups as often as you like, or manually back up your server with - you guessed it - one click.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-33297 size-full\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-backups-1.jpg\" alt=\"Website backup in Cloudways settings\" width=\"1417\" height=\"787\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-backups-1.jpg 1417w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-backups-1-300x167.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-backups-1-1024x569.jpg 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-backups-1-768x427.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-backups-1-848x471.jpg 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-backups-1-1140x633.jpg 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Cloudways-settings-backups-1-1170x650.jpg 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1417px) 100vw, 1417px\" /></p><h3>Performance and Speed</h3><p>Here’s where Cloudways really excels.</p><p>If you use their services, the WordPress site you make with Visual Composer will be hosted on probably the fastest WordPress hosting stack out there. Cloudways claims their uptime is 99.99%, and their loading speeds average out to 400 to 600 milliseconds. And that’s about how it worked for us.</p><p>Take a look at Visual Composer running on GTMetrix, Pingdom, and PageSpeed Insight here. We chose a Vultr server and tested a VC website on those tools.</p><h4>Resources that we used</h4><table style=\"width: 98.6519%; height: 384px;\"><tbody><tr style=\"height: 24px;\"><td style=\"height: 24px;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Cloudways Server Configuration</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height: 24px;\"><td style=\"height: 24px;\"><strong>Name</strong></td><td style=\"height: 24px;\"><strong>Specification</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height: 48px;\"><td style=\"height: 48px;\">Cloudways Server</td><td style=\"height: 48px;\">Vultr – High Frequency</td></tr><tr style=\"height: 24px;\"><td style=\"height: 24px;\">Datacenter location</td><td style=\"height: 24px;\">Seattle</td></tr><tr style=\"height: 24px;\"><td style=\"height: 24px;\">RAM</td><td style=\"height: 24px;\">2GB</td></tr><tr style=\"height: 24px;\"><td style=\"height: 24px;\">SSD Disk</td><td style=\"height: 24px;\">64GB</td></tr><tr style=\"height: 48px;\"><td style=\"height: 48px;\">Bandwidth Transfer</td><td style=\"height: 48px;\">2TB</td></tr><tr style=\"height: 24px;\"><td style=\"height: 24px;\">Processor</td><td style=\"height: 24px;\">1 Core</td></tr><tr style=\"height: 24px;\"><td style=\"height: 24px;\">Operating System</td><td style=\"height: 24px;\">Debian 9</td></tr><tr style=\"height: 24px;\"><td style=\"height: 24px;\">NGINX</td><td style=\"height: 24px;\">1.19</td></tr><tr style=\"height: 24px;\"><td style=\"height: 24px;\">Varnish</td><td style=\"height: 24px;\">6.0.7</td></tr><tr style=\"height: 24px;\"><td style=\"height: 24px;\">Apache</td><td style=\"height: 24px;\">2.4.25</td></tr><tr style=\"height: 24px;\"><td style=\"height: 24px;\">Database</td><td style=\"height: 24px;\">MariaDB 10.1</td></tr><tr style=\"height: 24px;\"><td style=\"height: 24px;\">PHP</td><td style=\"height: 24px;\">7.3</td></tr></tbody></table><h4>GTMetrix Performance Analysis</h4><p><a href=\"https://gtmetrix.com/reports/wordpress-643363-2096364.cloudwaysapps.com/PhpcRxMj/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-33299 size-full\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-gtmertix-performance-analysis-1.jpg\" alt=\"Cloudways performance on GTMetrix\" width=\"1895\" height=\"671\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-gtmertix-performance-analysis-1.jpg 1895w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-gtmertix-performance-analysis-1-300x106.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-gtmertix-performance-analysis-1-1024x363.jpg 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-gtmertix-performance-analysis-1-768x272.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-gtmertix-performance-analysis-1-1536x544.jpg 1536w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-gtmertix-performance-analysis-1-848x300.jpg 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-gtmertix-performance-analysis-1-1140x404.jpg 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-gtmertix-performance-analysis-1-1170x414.jpg 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1895px) 100vw, 1895px\" /></a></p><p><strong>Performance:</strong> 100%<br><strong>Structure:</strong> 96%<br><strong>LCP:</strong> 569ms<br><strong>TBT:</strong> 0ms<br><strong>CLS:</strong> 0</p><h4>Pingdom Performance Analysis</h4><p><a href=\"https://tools.pingdom.com/#5ecfa5794e000000\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-33300 size-full\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pingdom-performance-analysis-1.jpg\" alt=\"Cloudways performance on Pingdom\" width=\"1827\" height=\"855\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pingdom-performance-analysis-1.jpg 1827w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pingdom-performance-analysis-1-300x140.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pingdom-performance-analysis-1-1024x479.jpg 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pingdom-performance-analysis-1-768x359.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pingdom-performance-analysis-1-1536x719.jpg 1536w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pingdom-performance-analysis-1-848x397.jpg 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pingdom-performance-analysis-1-1140x533.jpg 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pingdom-performance-analysis-1-1170x548.jpg 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1827px) 100vw, 1827px\" /></a></p><p><strong>Performance Grade:</strong> 87<br><strong>Page Size:</strong> 968.4 KB<br><strong>Load Time:</strong> 295 ms<br><strong>Requests:</strong> 33</p><h4>PageSpeed Insight Performance Analysis</h4><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-33301 size-full\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pagespeed-performance-analysis-1.jpg\" alt=\"Cloudways performance on PageSpeed\" width=\"1893\" height=\"1160\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pagespeed-performance-analysis-1.jpg 1893w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pagespeed-performance-analysis-1-300x184.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pagespeed-performance-analysis-1-1024x627.jpg 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pagespeed-performance-analysis-1-768x471.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pagespeed-performance-analysis-1-1536x941.jpg 1536w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pagespeed-performance-analysis-1-848x520.jpg 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pagespeed-performance-analysis-1-1140x699.jpg 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pagespeed-performance-analysis-1-1170x717.jpg 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1893px) 100vw, 1893px\" /></p><p><strong>Overall Grade:</strong> 99<br><strong>FCP:</strong> 0.4s<br><strong>Speed Index:</strong> 1.9s<br><strong>LCP:</strong> 0.9s<br><strong>TTI:</strong> 0.4s<br><strong>TBT:</strong> 0ms<br><strong>CLS:</strong> 0</p><p><strong>Note:</strong> We used Cloudways managed WordPress hosting with dedicated servers and built-in cache plugins.</p><p>Part of the reason behind their performance is Cloudways’ partnership with five of the top cloud providers in the industry: Digital Cloud, Vultr, Linode, Google Cloud, and AWS. Plus, you can scale your server as your website grows and receives more traffic - all you have to do is allocate more RAM with 1-click. Those of you who spring for the Cloudways CDN will see further reduced latency as well. Then there’s the optimized stack consisting of Apache, NGINX, MySQL/MariaDB, all of which combine to produce a supersonic hosting environment.</p><p>You can read more about how Cloudways drastically improves uptime through one of their clients’ success stories <a href=\"https://www.cloudways.com/en/resources/case-studies/why-the-fuss\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a>.</p><h2>Setting Up Your Visual Composer Site On Cloudways</h2><p>Setting up on Cloudways is quite an intuitive process - launching your website is just a question of a few clicks. After selecting your cloud provider, you get to configure your server. Cloudways helps in this regard by suggesting a server size that would be able to handle your hosting needs based on your anticipated page view numbers. Or you can straight up specify your specifications in terms of bandwidth, RAM, processors, and storage.</p><p>We’ll show you the process of setting up your Visual Composer site on Cloudways, and we’ll also take you through the manual installation if that’s what you prefer.</p><h3>System Requirement for Visual Composer</h3><h4>Server and WordPress Requirements</h4><ul><li>Recommended PHP 7.2 or higher</li><li>MySQL version 5.6 or higher <em>(you can also run WordPress on MariaDB 10.0 or higher)</em></li><li>HTTPS support <em>(this has become mandatory in terms of good SEO)</em></li></ul><h4>Browser Requirements</h4><ul><li>Safari</li><li>Edge</li><li>Chrome</li><li>Firefox</li><li>iOS Safari</li></ul><h4>Devices Requirements</h4><ul><li>Mobile</li><li>Tablet</li><li>Laptop</li><li>Desktop</li></ul><p><strong>Note:</strong> Visit the Visual Composer <a href=\"https://visualcomposer.com/help/system-requirements/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">system requirement page</a> for more details.</p><h3>Launch Visual Composer on Cloudways in 1-Click</h3><p>Go to the <a href=\"https://visualcomposer.com/hosting/cloudways/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cloudways partnership page</a> on Visual Composer and click on the Get Started button.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-33302 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/visual-composer-cloudways-landing-page-1.png\" alt=\"Visual Composer Cloudways bundle landing page\" width=\"1010\" height=\"510\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/visual-composer-cloudways-landing-page-1.png 1010w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/visual-composer-cloudways-landing-page-1-300x151.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/visual-composer-cloudways-landing-page-1-768x388.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/visual-composer-cloudways-landing-page-1-848x428.png 848w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1010px) 100vw, 1010px\" /></p><p>You’ll be redirected toward the Cloudways x Visual Composer page.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-33303 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/launch-visual-composer-on-cloudways-landing-page-1.jpg\" alt=\"Launch Visual Composer on Cloudways landing page\" width=\"1898\" height=\"840\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/launch-visual-composer-on-cloudways-landing-page-1.jpg 1898w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/launch-visual-composer-on-cloudways-landing-page-1-300x133.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/launch-visual-composer-on-cloudways-landing-page-1-1024x453.jpg 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/launch-visual-composer-on-cloudways-landing-page-1-768x340.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/launch-visual-composer-on-cloudways-landing-page-1-1536x680.jpg 1536w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/launch-visual-composer-on-cloudways-landing-page-1-848x375.jpg 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/launch-visual-composer-on-cloudways-landing-page-1-1140x505.jpg 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/launch-visual-composer-on-cloudways-landing-page-1-1170x518.jpg 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1898px) 100vw, 1898px\" /></p><p>Click Launch Visual Composer Free, fill the signup form and click on the Start Free button.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-33304 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-account-sign-up-1.jpg\" alt=\"Create an account on Cloudways\" width=\"1920\" height=\"945\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-account-sign-up-1.jpg 1920w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-account-sign-up-1-300x148.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-account-sign-up-1-1024x504.jpg 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-account-sign-up-1-768x378.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-account-sign-up-1-1536x756.jpg 1536w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-account-sign-up-1-848x417.jpg 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-account-sign-up-1-1140x561.jpg 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-account-sign-up-1-1170x576.jpg 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" /></p><p>If you already have an account on Cloudways, then you can directly log in.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-33305 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-log-in-1.jpg\" alt=\"Log in for Cloudways\" width=\"1909\" height=\"867\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-log-in-1.jpg 1909w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-log-in-1-300x136.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-log-in-1-1024x465.jpg 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-log-in-1-768x349.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-log-in-1-1536x698.jpg 1536w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-log-in-1-848x385.jpg 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-log-in-1-1140x518.jpg 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-log-in-1-1170x531.jpg 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1909px) 100vw, 1909px\" /></p><p>After successfully logging in to Cloudways platform, click on the Add Server button. In the Application and Server Details section, you’ll see an option to select the WordPress application with Visual Composer. Enter the managed app and server names and select the project. This will enable your servers. You can then select the server according to your required size, specification, and location.</p><p>You can always scale your server size whenever required. At the bottom, you can see the hourly and monthly rates of the server. Launch the server according to your preferences.</p><p>After the server installation, click on the www option to access the application. The application management section will show you all the details related to your application. Go to the admin panel to access your WordPress Visual Composer website with the given URL, username, and password.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-33306 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-set-up-server-settings-1.jpg\" alt=\"Server setup in Cloudways settings\" width=\"1914\" height=\"575\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-set-up-server-settings-1.jpg 1914w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-set-up-server-settings-1-300x90.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-set-up-server-settings-1-1024x308.jpg 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-set-up-server-settings-1-768x231.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-set-up-server-settings-1-1536x461.jpg 1536w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-set-up-server-settings-1-848x255.jpg 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-set-up-server-settings-1-1140x342.jpg 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-set-up-server-settings-1-1170x351.jpg 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1914px) 100vw, 1914px\" /></p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-33307 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-settings-access-details-1.jpg\" alt=\"Access details in Cloudways settings\" width=\"1898\" height=\"899\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-settings-access-details-1.jpg 1898w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-settings-access-details-1-300x142.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-settings-access-details-1-1024x485.jpg 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-settings-access-details-1-768x364.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-settings-access-details-1-1536x728.jpg 1536w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-settings-access-details-1-848x402.jpg 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-settings-access-details-1-1140x540.jpg 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-settings-access-details-1-1170x554.jpg 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1898px) 100vw, 1898px\" /></p><p>After logging into the WordPress website, you’ll see Visual Composer is already installed on your site.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-33308 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/wordpress-admin-panel-visual-composer-1.jpg\" alt=\"Access Visual Composer in WordPress admin panel\" width=\"1898\" height=\"898\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/wordpress-admin-panel-visual-composer-1.jpg 1898w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/wordpress-admin-panel-visual-composer-1-300x142.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/wordpress-admin-panel-visual-composer-1-1024x484.jpg 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/wordpress-admin-panel-visual-composer-1-768x363.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/wordpress-admin-panel-visual-composer-1-1536x727.jpg 1536w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/wordpress-admin-panel-visual-composer-1-848x401.jpg 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/wordpress-admin-panel-visual-composer-1-1140x539.jpg 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/wordpress-admin-panel-visual-composer-1-1170x554.jpg 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1898px) 100vw, 1898px\" /></p><h3>Launch Visual Composer Manually on WordPress</h3><p>While there’s no need to install Visual Composer manually given the 1-click process, the manual installation process isn’t too hard either.</p><ol><li>Login to your WordPress website and go to WordPress Dashboard</li><li>Navigate to the Plugin option</li><li>Click on an Add New Plugin button</li><li>Search the plugin on the right-side search bar</li><li>Install the Visual Composer plugin</li><li>Activate it after installation</li></ol><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-33320 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/install-visual-composer-manually-from-wordpress-reposotory.png\" alt=\"Install Visual Composer from WordPress plugin repository\" width=\"1415\" height=\"630\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/install-visual-composer-manually-from-wordpress-reposotory.png 1415w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/install-visual-composer-manually-from-wordpress-reposotory-300x134.png 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/install-visual-composer-manually-from-wordpress-reposotory-1024x456.png 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/install-visual-composer-manually-from-wordpress-reposotory-768x342.png 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/install-visual-composer-manually-from-wordpress-reposotory-848x378.png 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/install-visual-composer-manually-from-wordpress-reposotory-1140x508.png 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/install-visual-composer-manually-from-wordpress-reposotory-1170x521.png 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1415px) 100vw, 1415px\" /></p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-33310 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/visual-composer-activation-on-wordpress-1.jpg\" alt=\"Visual Composer activation in WordPress\" width=\"827\" height=\"314\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/visual-composer-activation-on-wordpress-1.jpg 827w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/visual-composer-activation-on-wordpress-1-300x114.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/visual-composer-activation-on-wordpress-1-768x292.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 827px) 100vw, 827px\" /></p><p>Once you’re done with that, you can edit your WordPress site pages with Visual Composer. All WordPress sites are equipped with a pre-installed and pre-configured Breeze cache plugin to boost speed and performance. The server is optimized through Varnish.</p><h2>Why Doesn’t Cloudways Use cPanel?</h2><p>That Cloudways doesn’t use cPanel might come as a disappointment to some users, but to be honest, we found its control panel to be a cut above. Yes, cPanel is a popular tool for both first-time and professional users. But it’s a clunky tool - a visual mess that’s hard to navigate. Multiple aspects of its functionality are outdated, and the Cloudways control panel easily eclipses those.</p><p>For instance, cPanel does not offer in-built server monitoring tools. Instead, cPanel users have to purchase tools like MycPAdmin to secure their servers, or download free services such as Munin. Cloudways, on the other hand, offers ready server monitoring. Since this is a fully managed hosting provider service, you don’t have to worry about the hassles of server operation at all.</p><p>We’ve also run into our share of speed, functionality and security issues with cPanel. Its limited usage has often caused hosting lags, particularly if you start to go over their limit. In fact, it’s almost too easy to get kicked off the service if your usage is too high. And the end user is responsible for installing a firewall, configuring SSL and actively looking out for malware plugins that target cPanel security. All of these are non-issues for Cloudways whose dedicated resources allow for much faster hosting, and have integrated security at all levels of the platform.</p><p>Then there are the automatic backup limitations. While cPanel’s Dedicated Hosting and VPS plans do allow for automatic backups, the same does not hold true for all versions of the hosting service. And users with Reseller or Shared accounts cannot use their cPanel interface to automatically restore full backup; they instead have to submit tickets to cPanel’s Support department. This is very much in contrast to Cloudways’ more modern control panel – with this, you’re just a few clicks away from setting up automatic backups.</p><p>Plus, cPanel is sadly bereft of WP-CLI, which makes it so much easier for WordPress users to accomplish tasks like taking database backups and upgrades and managing numerous WordPress plugins, making it quite the nifty service. Utilizing WP-CLI on cPanel involves a difficult multi-stage installation process first. And it’s entirely possible that WP-CLI does not function with your WordPress install if a theme or plugin is conflicting with the load process. Cloudways, on the other hand, has WP-CLI pre-installed, thus negating the problem of conflicts with themes or other plugins on your site. Cloudways even has additional resources to help you get started, so you can manage WordPress plugins easily using WP-CLI.</p><p>For the TL;DR version, Cloudways easily scores above cPanel in terms of visual layout, ease of use, and advanced features.</p><h2>Customize Your Cloud Hosting Plan</h2><p>Perhaps what we liked best about Cloudways was the flexibility and choice it offers in terms of cloud hosting servers. They offer you a choice between five of the very best providers: DigitalOcean, Linode, Vultr, Amazon Web Services, or Google Cloud Platform. And it’s quite easy to move from one cloud provider to another, so if you realize down the line that Vultr’s the one for you, you can move to it from any of the others. That said, performance on each cloud doesn’t differ much, thanks to the overlaying Cloudways infrastructure.</p><p>Cloudways also offers pay-as-you-go rates, as mentioned earlier. What this means is that there are no restrictions on the number of websites you want to host, or installations, or traffic. You can scale as you like according to your requirements, and you’ll only pay for what you’ve consumed.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-33158\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pricing.jpg\" alt=\"Cloudways hosting pricing plans \" width=\"900\" height=\"534\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pricing.jpg 512w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/cloudways-pricing-300x178.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></p><h2>Cloudways vs the Competition</h2><p>Cloudways faces some pretty stiff competition in the hosting industry. Managed hosting providers like Kinsta, Siteground and WPEngine offer some excellent services as well and have their fair share of loyal fans. Of course, depending on your requirements and preferences, you might find one of those providers better. But we found Cloudways offers more value and better services for your Visual Composer website.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-33311 size-large\" src=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/hosting-poll-on-visual-composer-facebook-community-1-1024x901.jpg\" alt=\"Hosting poll on Visual Composer Facebook Community\" width=\"848\" height=\"746\" srcset=\"https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/hosting-poll-on-visual-composer-facebook-community-1-1024x901.jpg 1024w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/hosting-poll-on-visual-composer-facebook-community-1-300x264.jpg 300w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/hosting-poll-on-visual-composer-facebook-community-1-768x676.jpg 768w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/hosting-poll-on-visual-composer-facebook-community-1-848x746.jpg 848w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/hosting-poll-on-visual-composer-facebook-community-1-1140x1003.jpg 1140w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/hosting-poll-on-visual-composer-facebook-community-1-1170x1030.jpg 1170w, https://visualcomposer.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/hosting-poll-on-visual-composer-facebook-community-1.jpg 1217w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 848px) 100vw, 848px\" /></p><p>In fact, Cloudways consistently outperforms all three of the providers we mentioned in terms of ease of use, quality of support, and ease of setup, according to G2.com. It offers more choices of hosting providers, much more affordable rates across the board, and better scalability.</p><p>We found there are considerable performance gaps between Cloudways and the rest. Kinsta offers less control over your site and servers. Siteground has a reputation for not being able to handle larger websites. On the starter plan, Cloudways offers 1TB of bandwidth, and WPEngine only 50GB. Of course, all these hosting providers have their own competitive edges. But on the whole, we’d recommend Cloudways first to our Visual Composer users.</p><h2>Verdict</h2><p>Count us converts. We’re won over by the performance of WordPress and Visual Composer sites on Cloudways, and by how it hands easy control for web creators to save time and work more efficiently. Their customer service is excellent, and their speed and uptime are unrivaled. Their scaling mantra lets you grow your website as you need, and the server management is a breeze, as is the setup process. If you’re in the market for a hosting provider, you can’t go wrong with this.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/visual-composer-on-cloudways/\">Launch a Visual Composer Website on Cloudways in 1-Click</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://visualcomposer.com\">Visual Composer Website Builder</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/visual-composer-on-cloudways/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"WordPress Content Analysis Tool—Insights\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://visualcomposer.com/blog/wordpress-content-analysis-tool-insights/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_ex